<title>USA: United Video Satellite Q3 oper shr rises.</title>
<headline>United Video Satellite Q3 oper shr rises.</headline>
<dateline>TULSA, Okla. 1996-10-15</dateline>
<text>
<p>3 Mos ended 9/30     9 Mos ended 9/30</p>
<p>			  1996     1995	     1996	   1995</p>
<p> Revenues	  $117,701 $67,901	 $306,465     $183,869</p>
<p> Net income	   7,509   5,280	   22,579	 17,025</p>
<p>Net income, excluding</p>
<p>non-recurring</p>
<p>  charges	     8,885   6,861	   24,351	 19,137</p>
<p> Earnings per share  0.20    0.14	     0.61	   0.47</p>
<p> EPS excluding charges0.24   0.19	     0.66	   0.52</p>
<p> Wgtd avg shrs     37,042  36,738	   37,044	 36,562</p>
<p>EBITDA:</p>
<p> Prevue Networks(C) 4,470   4,417	     15,375     11,959</p>
<p> Prevue Interactive(1,535) (1,838)	    (3,790)    (3,751)</p>
<p> Superstar (A)    11,074    5,413	     25,348     15,221</p>
<p> UVTV		  4,360    3,991	     12,979     11,803</p>
<p> SSDS (B)	     (95)	717		1,085	  717</p>
<p> SpaceCom		965	 95		2,422	  410</p>
<p> Total(D)	   19,239   12,795	     53,419     36,359</p>
<p>		    (in thousands, except per share amounts)</p>
<p>(A)  Effective April 1, 1996, Superstar combined its retail home satellite dish programming operations with those of Liberty Media Corporation's Netlink division in a new consolidated entity that is owned 50% by UVSG.</p>
<p>(B)  On July 20, 1995, UVSG increased its ownership interest in SSDS from 10% to 70%.</p>
<p>(C)  After non-recurring charges of $1,380 in the quarter ended September 30, 1996.  $5,850 exclusive of non-recurring charges.</p>
<p>(D)  After non-recurring charges of $1,933 in the quarter and $2,433 for the nine months ended September 30, 1996 and $1,124 in the quarter and $1,313 for the nine months ended September 30, 1995.</p>
<p>-- New York Newsdesk 212 859-1610</p>
